msgid "Solution(s):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:366
msgid ""
"Level 1 (Critical Business Impact) and Level 2 (Major Business Impact) "
"support requests are received by on-call support staff, as well as three "
"supervisory staff who can monitor and escalate issues should the assigned"
" staff member appear to be unavailable or unable to respond to the "
"request within the SLA time allotted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:367
msgid ""
"As an additional safeguard, when an L1 or L2 escalation is reported, a "
"notification is sent via the company's internal Mattermost instance to "
"all qualified support staff to be aware of the issue, and any member can "
"step in if it seems follow-up may not be achieved within SLA "
"expectations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:369 ../../source/process/security.md:380
msgid "Mitigation(s):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:370
msgid ""
"Mattermost, Inc. employs support staff and engineers in multiple "
"timezones to increase availability, reduce response times and to reduce "
"the risk that key support staff would be unavailable to service emergency"
" requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:372
msgid "Downtime for Mattermost Hosted Push Notification Service (HPNS)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:375
msgid ""
"End users at customer sites deploying on HPNS do not receive mobile push "
"notifications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:378
msgid ""
"Mattermost, Inc. can re-deploy the service from backup to new "
"infrastructure, should its existing infrastructure suffer an outage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:381
msgid ""
"HPNS is available as open source software hosted on GitHub.com, allowing "
"enterprises an option to compile and self-host the service, should they "
"choose not to use HPNS hosted by Mattermost, Inc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:383
msgid ""
"Disruption of infrastructure providing support over email, online tickets"
" or Mattermost messaging during customer emergency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:386
msgid "Unable to communicate with Mattermost, Inc. support team during emergency"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:389
msgid ""
"Should a support channel be out-of-service, Mattermost, Inc. provides "
"redundant support options through email, online ticketing and (for "
"customers who have purchased core access premium support) online message "
"via Mattermost."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:391
msgid "Priority 2: Outages having immediate impact on business continuity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:393
msgid "Outage due to malicious software (viruses, works, trojans and similar)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:396 ../../source/process/security.md:404
msgid "Reduced capacity to continue business operations, depending on attack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:399
msgid ""
"Mattermost, Inc. staff uses multiple anti-virus solutions for detecting "
"and removing malicious software and regularly backs up key systems to "
"delete infected systems and re-deploy its infrastructure. Moreover, the "
"company uses a range of Windows, Mac and Linux-based workstations, "
"reducing the probability of a company-wide disruption from a single "
"strain of malicious software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:401
msgid "Outage due to online attacks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:407
msgid ""
"Mattermost, Inc. runs multiple monitoring and alerting services to detect"
" and isolate suspicious traffic and requests in order to minimize "
"downtime from potential online threats."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:408
msgid ""
"Should our self-hosted Mattermost instance be disrupted we can, if "
"needed, quickly re-deploy the solution within our VPN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:410
msgid "Disruption due to influenza pandemic or infectious disease outbreak"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:413
msgid "Reduced capacity to continue business operations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/process/security.md:416
msgid ""
"Mattermost, Inc. employs staff and engineers in multiple timezones and "
"geographic areas, reducing the risk of significant disruption that an "
"influenza pandemic or infectious disease outbreak would cause to business"
" operations."
msgstr ""

